ified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Neufbourg III was born about 1160, in Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Henri I de Neufbourg de Beaumont, was 41 and his mother, Marguerite de Sicile de Hauteville, was 23. He had at least 1 son with Jeanne. He died about 1243, at the age of 85."},"et":{"abt. 1160–Abt 1243":"umbes 1160–umbes 1243","1160–1243":"1160–1243","1170–Female":"1170–Surnud","–1199":"–1199","–1223":"–1223","–Female":"Surnud","1165–1243":"1165–1243","1120–1214":"1120–1214","1139–1178":"1139–1178","from 1170 to 1178":"1170 kuni 1178","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1139":"1139","abt. 1160":"umbes 1160","1214":"1214","1223":"1223","Abt 1243":"umbes 1243","1178":"1178","1243":"1243","1199":"1199","after February 1214":"pärast veebruari 1214","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Neufbourg, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Neufbourg, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"abt. 1160–Abt 1243":"noin 1160–noin 1243","1160–1243":"1160–1243","1170–Female":"1170–Kuollut","–1199":"–1199","–1223":"–1223","–Female":"Kuollut","1165–1243":"1165–1243","1120–1214":"1120–1214","1139–1178":"1139–1178","from 1170 to 1178":"vuodesta 1170 vuoteen 1178","about 1150":"noin 1150","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1139":"1139","abt. 1160":"noin 1160","1214":"1214","1223":"1223","Abt 1243":"noin 1243","1178":"1178","1243":"1243","1199":"1199","after February 1214":"helmikuu 1214 jälkeen","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Neuf